description:
Hard Time Season 2 is everything you'd want out of the continued story of wrongly convicted and oddly super powered Ethan Harrows.

Steve Gerber and Brian Hurtt give you more of the brutal prison life mixed with a dash of super human oddness they wonderfully delivered in "season one".

The series finale was handled extremely well, and although I'm sure there were many more issues planned out Hard Time has a solid and satisfying conclusion.
name: Hard Time Season Two

description:
While long in the publishing business, Ziff-Davis came late to comics and stayed only for a short time. 
  
To make their comics, almost none of which lasted for more than 4 issues, seem like they had been around longer they started almost all their comics numbering at issue # 10 
 
Little Al of the F.B.I. ran for only 2 issues and then was changed to Little Al of the Secret Service. 
 
All the covers were painted by  Norman Saunders.
name: Little Al of the FBI

description: Little Al of the FBI returns now a member of the Secret Service doing things no secret service agent has any business doing and with a new numbering on the retitled comic, and yet still no # 1, this one starting at # 2, then # 3, then skipping to # 10 before Little Al is heard from no more.
name: Little Al of the Secret Service

description:
A one-shot feautirng Interviews, commentary on the series from the creators, Q & A, characters profiles.

A 'zine, for the uninitiated, is short for "fanzine," and were DIY publications whose height of popularity was in the late 1970s with punk, though they enjoyed a resurgence in the '90s. The content of 'zines included engagement with various pop culture, rants, comics, and occasionally, some very personal writing. As technology developed, 'zines were supplanted by blogs and ezines, though they do still exist as of this writing in 2013. Peanut writer Ayun Halliday self-publishes a 'zine.
name: Gen 13 Zine

description:
Picking up where House of M and Wolverine: Origins & Endings left off! Armed with the one thing that could kill him, as well as key clues to his very existence, Logan embarks on the first leg of a long and bloody quest for vengeance against those who once enslaved him. No longer feeling the need to play it quiet, Logan's first strike elicits a Condition Critical response from the U.S. government. With no other choice, they drop their bomb - and you won't believe who it is! When Logan hits D.C., someone's going to be waiting for him.

description:
Wolverine's past with Captain America revealed! From the island nation of Madripoor to occupied France to the Tunisian desert, one of the most requested stories in Marvel history can finally be told! This WWII epic gives readers not only the details of the first meeting between Captain America and Wolverine, but also an insight into the first time Wolverine realizes that he, like Captain America, has the power to change his own destiny. But will he? Also featuring Bucky and Nick Fury, and Wolverine's long-awaited return to Madripoor in the present day! Don't miss out on this exploration of essential Marvel history!

description:
Marvel's two deadliest fighters go head-to-head in a battle to the finish! Two men, both products of the Weapon X program, both highly trained killers. One claims to be the best he is at what he does, though what he does isn't very nice - but the other is the Merc with a Mouth, and he might just have something to say about that claim! It's Deadpool vs. Wolverine, no quarter asked or given! But when both men can regenerate virtually any wound in a matter of moments, just how does either man expect to finish off his foe? And whoever wins will have to face down Daken, Wolverine's murderous son, who has a healing factor and aptitude for killing to match them both!
